\begin{abstract}
	In this paper, a Wireless Sensor Network (WSN) is used to implement a telemetry system with the equipments of a  photovoltaic boat. Using the EPOSMoteII as interface module of this network. The data will be sent to an Android tablet, where an application will be running. This application will have a Artificial Intelligence (AI) system implemented. With this AI, the boats pilot have a better knowledge of the vehicles situation. The results have shown a better efficiency as the pilot, with the data in his hands, knows better what to and not to do.

\textbf{\textit{Keywords} -} WSN Android, Intra-Vehicle WSN, Android AI, Embedded WSN
\end{abstract}

	\section{Introduction}

	Given Brazilâ€™s geographical location, is being generated an increasing demand for photovoltaic systems. In this context, photovoltaic boats are used to reduce 	operational costs and the polluter impact that diesels engines creates. These boats use electric devices to implement four main subsystems: power generation and storage, propulsion, management and communication. With the limited power supply, the first step for the success of these boats is the internal integration of the subsystems, using an effective (boats functionality and power efficiency) control network.
	
	Sensors and switches are mostly connected via a wired harness, which increases the weight and therefore the efficiency of the boat. In this scenario, a Wireless Sensor Network (WSN) is ideal to replace this wired connections. All the acquired data will be displayed in an Android application to guarantee a better knowledge of the boat situation.
	
